      "title": "Locus of perpendicular tangents",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Director Circle</strong></h3><p>The locus of the point of intersection of perpendicular tangents to a conic is known as its</p><p>director circle.</p><p>The director circle of a parabola is its directrix.</p><p><strong>Equation of the pair of tangents from a point to a parabola</strong></p><p>The combined equation of the pair of tangents drawn from a point to a parabola is $\\text{S}{{\\text{S}}^{\\text{ }\\!\\!'\\!\\!\\text{ }}}={{\\mathbf{T}}^{2}}$.</p><p><strong>Proof : </strong>Let $\\text{PQ}$ and $\\text{PR}$ be the tangents drawn from the point $\\text{P}\\left( {{\\text{x}}_{1}},{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)$ to the</p><p>parabola ${{\\text{y}}^{2}}=$ 4ax. Let $\\text{A}\\left( \\text{h},\\text{k} \\right)$ be any point on either tangent through $\\text{P}$. Then,</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"408\" height=\"243\"></p><p>equation of PA is</p><p>$\\begin{array}{*{35}{r}} \\text{y}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}} &amp; ~=\\frac{\\text{k}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}\\left( \\text{x}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right) \\\\ \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ or, }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ y} &amp; ~=\\left( \\frac{\\text{k}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}} \\right)\\text{x}+\\left( \\frac{\\text{h}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{k}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}} \\right) \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>This equation should be of the form</p><p>$\\text{y}=\\text{mx}+\\frac{\\text{a}}{\\text{m}}$</p><p>Comparing (i) and (ii), we get</p><p>$\\text{m}=\\frac{\\text{k}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ and }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\frac{\\text{a}}{\\text{m}}=\\frac{\\text{h}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{k}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}$</p><p><strong>Eliminating </strong>$\\text{m}$ from these two, we obtain</p><p>$\\text{a}=\\frac{\\text{k}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}\\times \\frac{\\text{h}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{kx}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}{\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}}}\\Rightarrow \\text{a}{{\\left( \\text{h}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)}^{2}}=\\left( \\text{k}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)\\left( \\text{h}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{k}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)$</p><p>Hence, the locus of the (h, k) i.e. equation of the pair of tangents, is</p><p>$\\begin{array}{*{35}{r}} \\text{a}{{\\left( \\text{x}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)}^{2}} &amp; ~=\\left( \\text{y}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)\\left( \\text{x}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{y}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right) \\\\ {} &amp; \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ or, }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\left( {{\\text{y}}^{2}}-4\\text{ax} \\right)\\left( \\text{y}_{1}^{2}-4\\text{ax} \\right)={{\\text{(y}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-2\\text{a}\\left( \\text{x}+{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)\\text{ }\\!\\!\\}\\!\\!\\text{ }}^{2}} \\\\ {} &amp; \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ or, }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\text{S}{{\\text{S}}^{\\text{ }\\!\\!'\\!\\!\\text{ }}}={{\\text{T}}^{2}}, \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>where $S={{y}^{2}}-4ax,{S}'=y_{1}^{2}-4a{{x}_{1}}$ and $T={{y}_{1}}-2a\\left( x+{{x}_{1}} \\right)$.</p><p><strong>REMARK : </strong>$\\text{S}=0$ is the equation of the curve, $\\text{{S}'}$ is obtained from $\\text{S}$ by replacing $\\text{x}$</p><p>by ${{\\text{x}}_{1}}$ and $\\text{y}$ by ${{\\text{y}}_{1}}$ and $\\text{T}=0$ is the equation of the tangent.</p>",
      "position": 0,
